  <title>Save PO file</title>

  <p>Each time you edit the PO file (by changing the translated string or the information in a header), an asterisk “*” sign appears before its name in the window title, or in the tab title if you are editing more than one PO file at the same time. This indicates that there are changes in the file. You can save your changes by pressing the  <gui style="button">Save</gui> in the header bar or using the <keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>S</key></keyseq> keyboard shortcut.</p>

 <p>To save the PO file with a different name, press the button next to <gui style="button">Save</gui> in the header bar or the <keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>Shift</key><key>S</key></keyseq> keyboard shortcut.
</p>

